##Industry Watch | Hubei Farmers Back to work, agricultural products out of Hubei, what on Earth

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The passage of agricultural products out of Hubei Epidemic area was restored, and a digital supply chain of "assisting agriculture and fighting epidemic disease" emerged. Alibaba is investing heavily in a "new infrastructure" for digital agriculture and opening up its plug-and-play digital capabilities to society during the epidemic to help fight epidemics and resume work

Mok Wan | man

On March 2,40 tonnes of navel oranges from Zigui County, Hubei Province, were shipped out of Hubei for the first time after the outbreak. This time Navel Orange's fortunes have been reversed thanks to a new infrastructure built with digital technology.

"when the epidemic first broke out, the wholesale markets in Beijing and Shandong stopped the entry of agricultural products from Hubei. Zigui Navel Oranges are harvest time, but they can not be sold,"Lan Huafeng, director of the agricultural and Rural Bureau in Zigui County, told Caijing.

The main reason for the suspension is the fear of the new coronavirus and the epidemic prevention. "In fact, the virus needs a host to survive. Plants are completely different from people. Without the host of the virus in plants, the virus will not survive in plants, " Deng Xiuxin, deputy dean of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and "academician of citrus, " explained to Caijing.

In addition to the market for agricultural products in Hubei Hesitancy, picking, processing, transportation, sales of each link of manpower shortage, logistics is not smooth, but also restrict the export of Zigui Navel Orange objective factors. At least 170,000 tonnes of mature navel oranges could not be picked and sold across Zigui because of the outbreak.

Zigui County has issued an urgent appeal to fruit distributors and e-commerce companies across the country to save the navel oranges from a slow market. Soon, Alibaba came to the rescue, working with Zigui County to create a digital supply chain for a particular period of time. Zigui Navel Oranges, the first to be shipped through a digital supply chain, are now sold on platforms such as Taobao and Hema Xiansheng.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The mature Zigui Navel Orange is going national through Alibaba's digital agriculture supply chain

It is understood that the Zigui help-seeking information, since the outbreak of the Alibaba received one of the many unsalable information. In order to help local timely sales, Alibaba in 20 provinces across the country to open a "love to help farmers line. ". As of March 5, the line had sold 90,000 tons of unmarketable agricultural products.

It is a short term goal to help farmers connect production and marketing during the epidemic, while in the long term, combining agricultural technology with Ali's digital technology to raise the level of digitalization in agriculture, only then can help "three agriculture" use the Internet and the digital technology foundation ability to enhance own compression resistance and the competitive superiority.

Under the sudden epidemic situation, the traditional agricultural product line sale pattern has exposed its limitation and the frailty. Zigui's navel oranges were eventually "rescued" thanks to a supply chain built by Ali using digital technology. From picking in the fields to serving at the dinner tables of people across the country, this invisible infrastructure is at work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Fashan, a fruit farmer, has sold a third of his navel oranges through Alibaba

In recent years, technological advances have driven the transformation of the economic development model, and the old infrastructure has been unable to fully meet the new demands of the digital economy. Zigui's Navel Orange Story shows the urgency of building new infrastructure, represented by 5G networks, cloud computing and artificial intelligence.

Discussion on the color change of "Hubei" in agricultural product market

At 10 a.m. on January 23, the city of Wuhan was sealed off. The move made the nation instantly aware of the seriousness of the new outbreak, with Zhejiang, Guangdong and Hunan initiating a first-level response to major public health emergencies. Strict anti-epidemic measures have been taken all over the country, restricting not only Hubei people, but also Hubei's agricultural products.

According to a document provided by LAN Huafeng to CAIJING reporters, on January 23, the Shandong Linyi Jiaxing fruit market issued a notice to all business departments: In order to strengthen the prevention and control of the new coronavirus, starting today, hubei Fruit Logistics vehicles are prohibited from entering the Linyi Jiaxing fruit market.

The next day, on January 24, the Beijing News reported that the Xinfadi market, the nation's largest agricultural product distribution center, had run out of vegetables and fruits from Wuhan, and suspended Hubei Agricultural products from entering the Xinfadi market.

"We were very worried when we saw the news, " Lan said. "This kind of document has played a bad role. Many markets have actually started boycotting Hubei's agricultural products, even though they don't have clear regulations. " Yang Yong, the county chief of Zigui County, also said, "Our oranges taste good, but consumers are concerned because of the outbreak. "

The so-called "land of the Chinese Navel Orange" , Hubei and Zigui, is not immune. Located in the western part of Hubei Province and at the head of the Three Gorges Dam on the Bank of the Xiling Gorge River, Zigui County is the famous home of the Chinese Navel Orange, the production pattern of fresh orange is available all the year round. In early February, there were 48,500 tons of fully mature newhall Navel, peach leaf and ponkan oranges in the county, in addition to the 25,000 tons of oranges that will be on the market in February, according to the Zigui County Agricultural and Rural Bureau, lunwan Navel Orange (70,000 tons) and Xia orange (30,000 tons) will go on sale from the end of April to mid-to-late May.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In early February, Zigui County had 48,500 tonnes of all kinds of citrus ripe on the trees.

Sales of Navel oranges have been blocked, and Deng Xiuxin, a "academician of citrus" , has had his cell phone smashed. In Zigui, many fruit farmers have Deng Xiuxin mobile phone number, fruit is not sweet, fruit unsalable, a phone call to "academician Deng. ".

"fruits don't grow legs and can not infect people, " Deng xiuxin quickly "refutes the rumor. " "through scientific epidemic prevention and strict quality control, fruits from Hubei are safe. " He said fruits and vegetables are impossible to infect people, suspending logistics, it's just that people who transport fruit carry the virus.

Deng Xiuxin has special feelings for Zigui. Since the 1980s, he and his team have been based in Zigui, helping farmers solve technical problems, helping the government connect industrial resources and going around "selling" . He brought in late-night citrus varieties from abroad, brought in loans to build a state-of-the-art sorting center, and led Zigui from citrus farming to citrus culture and tourism.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Twenty years ago, immigrants from Zigui transplanted navel oranges to their new home

After the farmers asked for help, Deng Xiuxin and Zigui County decided to report back to Alibaba. On February 20th Zigui County's rural and Agricultural Bureau sent a letter to Alibaba asking for procurement and sales support. After more than a week, the time was ripe. Zigui was listed as one of 11 low-risk counties (cities and districts) in Hubei Province on Feb. 29, when the province issued its first assessment report on the risk level of the epidemic.

"ALIBABA can help us sell navel oranges, not only to solve the sales problem, but more importantly, in the case of the epidemic, to dispel the psychological concerns of consumers about Hubei Fruit, " said Lan. "ALIBABA has helped us to set us on a path to prosperity -- if it can sell, it is a secure agricultural product. "

The digital supply chain starts in the field

Under the current epidemic situation, in order to transport Hubei agricultural products out of Hubei and sell them to the whole country, it is necessary to dispel the doubts of the market on the one hand, and solve the problems of picking, processing, transportation and sale on the other hand.

At the beginning of February, Zigui County issued an open letter of help, "inviting all the fruit distributors in the country to come to Zigui to purchase and sell Zigui Navel Oranges, to contribute to the prevention and control of diseases in Hubei and to increase the income of citrus farmers in Zigui. " But at this moment, wholesalers are reluctant to venture into Hubei. Traditional wholesalers need to enter the production area to see the goods, face-to-face transactions; at present do not see the goods, logistics, quality control is difficult to land, they have more than they can do.

Zigui is Alibaba's First National Base for digital agriculture. Since 2018, Zigui has been building a digital supply chain that uses digital technology to improve efficiency in production, quality control, transport and distribution, but the chain has also been disrupted by the outbreak.

After receiving a call for help from Zigui County, Alibaba decided to urgently rebuild its digital supply chain.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In 2018, Alibaba set up its first digital agricultural base in Zigui, Hubei Province.

Zigui Navel Orange Export, the focus is not only in the final "sales" , the field on the picking, to a great extent to test the coordination of local epidemic prevention and resumption of work.

"farmers are afraid to leave their villages. Local governments are also afraid to let people gather on a large scale, and many villages are still sealed off, " Wang Wei, a senior operations expert at Alibaba's Ministry of Digital Agriculture, told CAIJING, "ALIBABA's digital agriculture supply chain can aggregate orders from the sales end in advance, use the sales plan to backtrack the pickings at the production end, figure out how many people are needed, and then work with the Zigui County government to get them back to the orchard. "

The epidemic prevention measures are not relaxed at the time of picking, and each orchard strictly follows the rule of no more than 15 people. "We have one hand on epidemic prevention and the other on production, " Lan said. "fruit farmers have to wear face masks and take body temperature twice a day when picking in different areas. "

After harvesting, navel oranges are shipped to local processing plants for sorting and packaging, and sold on Hema fresh, e-commerce platforms and in Hubei Province, depending on the quality. At this stage, workers who are also sorting and packing. In order to recruit enough people, alibaba hired local villagers to return to work at a high price.

For the quality control problem, Nail on-line "cloud quality control" , from farmers pick to enter the processing plant to follow the whole process, monitoring farmers epidemic prevention and protection measures, monitoring the picking process of the norms, monitoring the fruit diameter, smoothness, and on-site evaluation of the sweet and Sour degree of cloud. In addition to cloud control, randomly selected navel oranges were also sent to the quality control center of Alibaba's Digital Agriculture Division for testing by Alibaba and a third-party professional quality control agency.

In terms of logistics, Yang Yong said, "many express delivery companies that need to transit through Jingzhou are just jumping the gun because of the epidemic, and the road is not completely clear. " To this end, Alibaba's CAINIAO joint logistics partner, a special green passage out of Zigui. In the special period, the logistics cost rises obviously, the CAINIAO and its system of Zhongtong, Shentong, Yantong open the public welfare linkage mechanism, in the premise of ensuring the driver's income, reduce the logistics cost as far as possible.

"since March 3, Zigui has sent 80,000 catties of navel oranges to the whole country, and Wuhan's boxes of Ma Xiansheng have been delivered, " said Wang, who said the fruit would be on sale until May.

Promoting on-line sale of agricultural products by means of information technology

"One of the main functions of digitalization in agriculture is to make information symmetrical, " said Deng Xiuxin. Before, agricultural products were in mountain ditches, and farmers didn't know who wanted them. The products were shipped to wholesale areas in big cities, to retailers, and then to stores, it takes a few moves to get to the consumer. Now e-commerce platforms are bridging the gap between producers and consumers. It's more direct and convenient. "Digital Agriculture is definitely the general direction of agricultural development, " he said

At present, Zigui has become one of Hubei province's highest level of e-commerce counties. In 2018,1,592 e-commerce companies sold Zigui Navel oranges through Alibaba, the largest single sale of Zigui Navel oranges in the country, according to the agricultural and Rural Bureau of Zigui County.

After launching its $1,000-per-mu plan in 2018 and setting up its first digital agricultural base in Zigui, Alibaba set up its agriculture office in 2019, overall planning by Taobao, tmall, alipay, Hema, rookie and other more than 20 business digital farming network.

This digital farming system has played a special role in this outbreak. On February 6, Alibaba launched the "love to help farmers program" and set up a billion "love to help farmers fund" to pool the power of the digital economy to create an emergency "love to help farmers line" for the country's unsalable agricultural products, online and offline directly for the national market.

On the afternoon of February 18, the joint defense and Joint Control Mechanism of the State Council held a press conference to introduce the work of "vegetable basket" to ensure stable production and supply. Song Danyang, deputy director of the Department of Marketing and Information Technology in the Ministry of Agriculture, said that making full use of information technology to promote online sales of agricultural products is one of the four key measures for docking production and marketing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In Alibaba's digital farming base, farmers use mobile phones to "grow vegetables. ".

At present, agriculture is still in a backward position in the development of China's digital economy. The sudden outbreak may make more and more agricultural practitioners realize the functions and advantages of digital infrastructure in the industry chain can not be replaced. After the outbreak, thousands of vegetable greenhouses have sprung up all over the country. On February 15, the biggest "village sowing day" in history, 10,000 farmers started broadcasting vegetables collectively. In the era of digital agriculture, data become the new agricultural means, mobile phones become the new agricultural tools, live broadcast become the new agricultural activities. And the intelligent mobile office platform like nail also provides an efficient channel for farmers to feed back the unsalable information of agricultural products to the "love and help-the-farmers hotline" . Some of the past only under the line of agricultural products, emergency docking on Taobao.

Digital villages have become a national strategy. According to the Digital Agriculture Rural Development Plan (2019-2025) issued by the Ministry of Agriculture and the Office of the Central Network Security and Informatization Commission on January 20, Internet enterprises should play a central leading role, drive agricultural and rural modernization with digital guidance. One of the projected targets is for the agricultural digital economy to grow from 7.3 per cent of agricultural value added in 2018 to 15 per cent in 2025, with an average annual growth rate of 10.8 per cent.

In the process of digitalization of agriculture, there is great potential for the science and technology enterprises which already possess the basic ability of digital technology. After the outbreak, a new generation of digital infrastructure will be the new direction, said Jang Yong, Chairman of the Board's Chief Executive. Digital infrastructure is the new infrastructure, is becoming a new direction of investment and development. "The great value of digitalization has already taken root in people's minds. Alibaba not only has to take more social responsibility in the crisis, but also has to create opportunities for the next step of economic development. "
